==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cistern
<hw>Cis"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cisterne</ets>, OF. <ets>cisterne</ets>, F. <ets>cisterne</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>cisterna</ets>, fr. <ets>cista</ets> box, chest. See
<er>Cist</er>, and cf. <er>chest</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
artificial reservoir or tank for holding water, beer, or other
liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A natural reservoir; a hollow place containing
water.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The wide <xex>cisterns</xex> of the lakes.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Blackmore.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

